    {
      "name": "Supra-Conscious States of Yoga",
      "timestamp": "00:20",
      "gurunath_words": "The Alpha and the Omega of yoga is self-realization. Yoga is the ascent of one's consciousness through ever more refined and ever more expanded spheres of mind to get to the goddess lying at the core of one's own being."
    },
    {
      "name": "The Role of Abhyasa and Vairagya",
      "timestamp": "00:40",
      "gurunath_words": "Yoga is brought about and made successful by abhyasa and vairagya. The meaning of abhyasa is to move towards the goal with intensity towards God, unruffled by emotions or outward distractions. Vairagya means non-attachment to the objects of the five senses."
    },
    {
      "name": "Misconceptions About Yoga",
      "timestamp": "02:24",
      "gurunath_words": "There is a widely prevalent misconception in the West regarding the nature and purpose of yoga. A person practicing asanas and postural integration to improve his health says he is practicing yoga. It's true that people in innocent ignorance vulgarize yoga since a practice of asanas and postures does not constitute the real practice of yoga."
    },
    {
      "name": "Samadhi and Its True Nature",
      "timestamp": "01:48",
      "gurunath_words": "When we consider the state of Samadhi, we must be aware of the fact that this technique is not only the higher form of yoga but its very essence. A great rishi stated, 'Yoga is Samadhi.'"
    },
    {
      "name": "Kriya Yoga and Pranayama",
      "timestamp": "12:00",
      "gurunath_words": "The science of Kriya yoga pranayama offers the inhaled pranic breath into the exhaled apanic breath and vice versa. By this process, the yogi neutralizes the two life currents of pran and apan."
    }
  ],
  "sacred_sayings": [
    {
      "quote": "The Alpha and the Omega of yoga is self-realization."
    },
    {
      "quote": "Yoga is Samadhi."
    },
    {
      "quote": "The science of yoga commends itself to the foremost minds of East and West."
    },
    {
      "quote": "Pranayama is therefore life control and not breath control."
    }
  ]
}

